Hello and thanks for the invitation to the elite-server owner page haha...

Wish me luck? What do you think about it?

item.title: 2-3 days to number one on the top servers!
item.dc:creator: @smkscape smkscape
item.description:
@smkscape wrote:

[quote=“Moparisthebest, post:35, topic:384513”][quote author=smkscape link=topic=480277.msg3595599#msg3595599 date=1305048796]

Then link me to where you saw they are pay to use.

There are voters, almost auto. Loads proxys and all you have to do is type in the recaptcha. Can vote like 500 times in 10 minutes. People were selling on HF.

But there is no way to combat actual human interaction, is there?

No, but you could make it harder to do for them. Like good crypt the page, so they cannot find the recaptcha information.

If your browser can ‘find’ the info, so can anything else, completely automatically.

But you could encrypt it right, so when they view the page source they have to decrypt it. And much people have no idea how to. So then you already are a step ahead.
[/quote]
You can encrypt it or do anything else you like to it, but if you want the browser to be able to show it, you have to put all your code to decrypt it right out there in the public for the browser to use. The bottom line is if the browser can get the info, so can anything else, easily.[/quote]

Alright. It already checks on IP right?

Read full topic
